Description: ELDdevices.net was born in 2017 from the desire of a trucker to share his knowledge with his colleagues.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Every time, you arrived at the shipper or receiver you were kept waiting. At times it was 2 hours and at times it was as long as 5 hours. Despite all of that, trucking and being an owner-operator proved to be lucrative in terms of earnings and life experiences. However, after a while, life on the road began to take a toll on me. If that wasn’t enough, in Dec 2017 the ELD mandate came into effect and that made the life of every owner operator, every trucker, and any company driver, a lot more difficult. I decided to research the matter, I was hoping to find a solution that would help me avoid the eld device mandate. I was not able to find such a workaround. However, in my research, I came across different benefits of different devices. I decided that it would be a good idea for me to share all that I have learned with other fellow truckers. That is how elddevices.net came to life. My name is Robert, a lifetime trucker and eld devices, enthusiast. I strongly hope that this site would help other fellow truckers. If there is anything we can do to improve our site, feel free to share this with us.

Description: Our technology allows us to custom engrave any image (3D-Print) inside glass material using diode-laser. No outer surface gets altered.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: We are a glass design team specializing in latest German-engineered laser technology for 'inner' custom glass engraving and cutting. With years of experience in print and graphic design and ability to supply and customize most unique glass types makes us a 'one-stop-shop' for any of your custom glass design needs. We carry a database containing millions of royalty free stock photo, vector, graphics and pattern images to fit any project. GLASSarium Laser Machine has been particularly developed for the sub-surface engraving (3D-Printing) inside glass or crystal material using diode-laser. Specific technique of 'inner' engraving is the feature that the image is laser-engraved on the inside of the glass, no outer surface being altered in any way or form. Under normal conditions, the engraving below the surface is non-destructive, which results in a lifetime labeling that cannot be removed and will stay inside the glass forever, with no fade or loss of contrast. Both surfaces finish will always remain in its original condition. Almost anything can be laser-imprinted into the glass- from logos to landscapes. Each engraved piece is 'one of-a-kind', unless mass-produced. Most of the labelling is possible without using any consumable supplies.  Intensive research work, a high quality awareness and laser industry development are the reasons why this amazing technology is available to us today.    No radiation, residue or chemicals are produced during or after the GLASSarium laser engraving process.

Description: GateBridge Investments seeks investments by taking equity stakes in companies in partnership with a management team.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: GateBridge Investments is a private investment and advisory firm backed by John Rodakis and several other high net worth individual and institutional investors. GateBridge seeks investments where it can earn long-term, high rates of return on its capital, by taking equity stakes in companies in partnership with a management team. While the primary focus is on technology related companies, they will consider and have experience with non-technology companies as well. Because it is not an institutional fund, GateBridge can be much more flexible than a traditional private equity firm and can consider a broad range of investments sizes: from very small early stage investments to arraigning complex large transactions requiring $100 million of capital or more. Also, because GateBridge does not operate a fund with a finite life, it can take a much longer term perspective on its investments than a traditional private equity fund which may need to exit an investment quickly to be able to raise it's next fund.
